               <h2>Introduction</h2> 
               <p>A Smartphone is a handheld device that <em>revolutionized</em> the way in which humans communicate with each other and perform day to day tasks. They have made our life a lot easier, smartphones are used by us nowadays nearly all the time as they provide us with the mobility of handheld device and the power of personal computer.
                </p>
                <p>Most of the smartphones nowadays use touchsceen as  the main input source. They have large screens and cameras that could put most point and shoots to shame. They provide a <strong>vast</strong> range of functionality ranging from directions to playing games
               </p>
            </article>
               <aside>    
                   <h2>The Beginning</h2>
                   <figure>
                       <img src="simon.jpg" height="208" width="208" alt="IBM Simon" />
                       <figcaption>IBM Simon</figcaption>
                   </figure>
                   <blockquote cite="http://www.pcmag.com/encyclopedia/term/51537/smartphone">In 1994, IBM and BellSouth introduced the heavy and pricey Simon Personal Communicator, a phone/PDA touted as the first smartphone. Amassing a large audience in the 2000s, BlackBerry became the popular corporate smartphone; however, in 2007, the iPhone changed the industry forever.
                   </blockquote>
               </aside>
